result: Paper-and-pencil math calculation skills, ranging from basic operations with integers to geometry, algebra, and calculus problems was Average overall.
Written spelling from dictations was Average and ranked at the 37th percentile, indicating performance as good as or better than 37% of same-age peers from the general population.
An estimate of premorbid verbal ability level was classified as Average and ranked at the 58th percentile.
Reading comprehension skills at the level of word, sentence, and passage was classified as Average and ranked at the 70th percentile.
A composite score of decoding and comprehension that balances word-level and text-level reading skills fell in the Average range.
